<span class="s1">&lt;/tbody&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/table&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">This module contains several simple classes to be used within games. There is</span>
<span class="s0">the main Sprite class and several Group classes that contain Sprites. The use</span>
<span class="s0">of these classes is entirely optional when using pygame. The classes are fairly</span>
<span class="s0">lightweight and only provide a starting place for the code that is common to</span>
<span class="s0">most games.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The Sprite class is intended to be used as a base class for the different types</span>
<span class="s0">of objects in the game. There is also a base Group class that simply stores</span>
<span class="s0">sprites. A game could create new types of Group classes that operate on</span>
<span class="s0">specially customized Sprite instances they contain.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The basic Sprite class can draw the Sprites it contains to a Surface. The</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Group.draw()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">method requires that each Sprite have a </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Surface.image</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span>
<span class="s0">attribute and a </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Surface.rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">. The </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Group.clear()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">method requires these</span>
<span class="s0">same attributes, and can be used to erase all the Sprites with background.</span>
<span class="s0">There are also more advanced Groups: </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.sprite.RenderUpdates()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">and</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.sprite.OrderedUpdates()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Lastly, this module contains several collision functions. These help find</span>
<span class="s0">sprites inside multiple groups that have intersecting bounding rectangles. To</span>
<span class="s0">find the collisions, the Sprites are required to have a </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Surface.rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span>
<span class="s0">attribute assigned.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The groups are designed for high efficiency in removing and adding Sprites to</span>
<span class="s0">them. They also allow cheap testing to see if a Sprite already exists in a</span>
<span class="s0">Group. A given Sprite can exist in any number of groups. A game could use some</span>
<span class="s0">groups to control object rendering, and a completely separate set of groups to</span>
<span class="s0">control interaction or player movement. Instead of adding type attributes or</span>
<span class="s0">bools to a derived Sprite class, consider keeping the Sprites inside organized</span>
<span class="s0">Groups. This will allow for easier lookup later in the game.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprites and Groups manage their relationships with the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">add()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">and</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">remove()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">methods. These methods can accept a single or multiple targets for</span>
<span class="s0">membership. The default initializers for these classes also takes a single or</span>
<span class="s0">list of targets for initial membership. It is safe to repeatedly add and remove</span>
<span class="s0">the same Sprite from a Group.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">While it is possible to design sprite and group classes that don't derive from</span>
<span class="s0">the Sprite and AbstractGroup classes below, it is strongly recommended that you</span>
<span class="s0">extend those when you add a Sprite or Group class.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprites are not thread safe. So lock them yourself if using threads.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The base class for visible game objects. Derived classes will want to</span>
<span class="s0">override the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprite.update()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">and assign a </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprite.image</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">and</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprite.rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">attributes. The initializer can accept any number of Group</span>
<span class="s0">instances to be added to.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">When subclassing the Sprite, be sure to call the base initializer before</span>
<span class="s0">adding the Sprite to Groups. For example:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">A simple container for Sprite objects. This class can be inherited to create</span>
<span class="s0">containers with more specific behaviors. The constructor takes any number of</span>
<span class="s0">Sprite arguments to add to the Group. The group supports the following</span>
<span class="s0">standard Python operations:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight-default notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;ow&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">in</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;      &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">test</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;k&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">if</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">a</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprite</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;ow&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">is</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">contained</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;nb&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">len</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;     &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">the</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">number</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">of</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprites</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">contained</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;nb&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">bool</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">test</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;k&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">if</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;nb&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">any</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprites</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">are</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">contained</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;nb&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">iter</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">iterate</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">through</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;nb&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">all</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">the</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprites</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The Sprites in the Group are ordered only on python 3.6 and higher.</span>
<span class="s0">Below python 3.6 drawing and iterating over the Sprites is in no particular order.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Return a list of all the Sprites this group contains. You can also get an</span>
<span class="s0">iterator from the group, but you cannot iterate over a Group while</span>
<span class="s0">modifying it.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">copy() -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Group</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Creates a new Group with all the same Sprites as the original. If you</span>
<span class="s0">have subclassed Group, the new object will have the same (sub-)class as</span>
<span class="s0">the original. This only works if the derived class's constructor takes</span>
<span class="s0">the same arguments as the Group class's.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Erases the Sprites used in the last </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Group.draw()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">call. The</span>
<span class="s0">destination Surface is cleared by filling the drawn Sprite positions with</span>
<span class="s0">the background.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The background is usually a Surface image the same dimensions as the</span>
<span class="s0">destination Surface. However, it can also be a callback function that</span>
<span class="s0">takes two arguments; the destination Surface and an area to clear. The</span>
<span class="s0">background callback function will be called several times each clear.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Draws all the Sprites to the surface, the same as </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Group.draw()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">. This</span>
<span class="s0">method also returns a list of Rectangular areas on the screen that have</span>
<span class="s0">been changed. The returned changes include areas of the screen that have</span>
<span class="s0">been affected by previous </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Group.clear()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">calls.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The returned Rect list should be passed to </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.display.update()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span>
<span class="s0">This will help performance on software driven display modes. This type of</span>
<span class="s0">updating is usually only helpful on destinations with non-animating</span>
<span class="s0">backgrounds.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">This class derives from </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.sprite.RenderUpdates()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">. <span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">This group is fully compatible with </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.sprite.Sprite&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.sprite.Sprite</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Simple base class for visible game objects.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">You can set the default layer through kwargs using 'default_layer' and an</span>
<span class="s0">integer for the layer. The default layer is 0.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">If the sprite you add has an attribute _layer then that layer will be used.</span>
<span class="s0">If the **kwarg contains 'layer' then the sprites passed will be added to</span>
<span class="s0">that layer (overriding the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">sprite.layer</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">attribute). If neither sprite</span>
<span class="s0">has attribute layer nor **kwarg then the default layer is used to add the</span>
<span class="s0">sprites.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">There is a special property, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">GroupSingle.sprite</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, that accesses the</span>
<span class="s0">Sprite that this Group contains. It can be None when the Group is empty. The</span>
<span class="s0">property can also be assigned to add a Sprite into the GroupSingle</span>
<span class="s0">container.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig sig-object py title&quot; </span><span class="s2">id</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.sprite.spritecollide&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-prename descclassname&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.sprite.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-name descname&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">spritecollide</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-paren&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-paren&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;headerlink&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.sprite.spritecollide&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;Permalink to this definition&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0"></span><span class="s1">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line-block&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;summaryline&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Find sprites in a group that intersect another sprite.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">spritecollide(sprite, group, dokill, collided = None) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Sprite_list</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Return a list containing all Sprites in a Group that intersect with another</span>
<span class="s0">Sprite. Intersection is determined by comparing the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprite.rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span>
<span class="s0">attribute of each Sprite.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The dokill argument is a bool. If set to True, all Sprites that collide will</span>
<span class="s0">be removed from the Group.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The collided argument is a callback function used to calculate if two</span>
<span class="s0">sprites are colliding. it should take two sprites as values, and return a</span>
<span class="s0">bool value indicating if they are colliding. If collided is not passed, all</span>
<span class="s0">sprites must have a </span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">rect</span><span class="s4">&amp;quot; </span><span class="s0">value, which is a rectangle of the sprite area,</span>
<span class="s0">which will be used to calculate the collision.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">collided callables:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight-default notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">collide_rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">collide_rect_ratio</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">collide_circle</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">collide_circle_ratio</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">collide_mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Example:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight-python notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;c1&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0"># See if the Sprite block has collided with anything in the Group block_list</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;c1&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0"># The True flag will remove the sprite in block_list</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">blocks_hit_list</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;o&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">=</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;o&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">sprite</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;o&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">spritecollide</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">player</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">block_list</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; <span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">A callable class that checks for collisions between two sprites, using a</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">A callable class that checks for collisions between two sprites, using a</span>
<span class="s0">scaled version of the sprites radius.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Is created with a floating point ratio, the instance is then intended to be</span>
<span class="s0">passed as a collided callback function to the *collide functions.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">A ratio is a floating point number - 1.0 is the same size, 2.0 is twice as</span>
<span class="s0">big, and 0.5 is half the size.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The created callable tests for collision between two sprites, by testing to</span>
<span class="s0">see if two circles centered on the sprites overlap, after scaling the</span>
<span class="s0">circles radius by the stored ratio. If the sprites have a </span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">radius</span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span>
<span class="s0">attribute, that is used to create the circle, otherwise a circle is created</span>
<span class="s0">that is big enough to completely enclose the sprites rect as given by the</span>
<span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">rect</span><span class="s4">&amp;quot; </span><span class="s0">attribute. Intended to be passed as a collided callback function to</span>
<span class="s0">the *collide functions. Sprites must have a </span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">rect</span><span class="s4">&amp;quot; </span><span class="s0">and an optional </span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">radius</span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span>
<span class="s0">attribute.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Tests for collision between two sprites, by testing if their bitmasks</span>
<span class="s0">overlap (uses </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;mask.html#pygame.mask.Mask.overlap&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.mask.Mask.overlap()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Returns the point of intersection</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="s0">). If the sprites have a</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">attribute, it is used as the mask, otherwise a mask is created from</span>
<span class="s0">the sprite's </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">image</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">(uses </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;mask.html#pygame.mask.from_surface&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.mask.from_surface()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Creates a Mask from the given surface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="s0">). Sprites must</span>
<span class="s0">have a </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">attribute; the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">attribute is optional.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The first point of collision between the masks is returned. The collision</span>
<span class="s0">point is offset from </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">sprite1</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">'s mask's topleft corner (which is always</span>
<span class="s0">(0, 0)). The collision point is a position within the mask and is not</span>
<span class="s0">related to the actual screen position of </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">sprite1</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">This function is intended to be passed as a </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">collided</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">callback function</span>
<span class="s0">to the group collide functions (see </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.sprite.spritecollide&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.sprite.spritecollide&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">spritecollide()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.sprite.groupcollide&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.sprite.groupcollide&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">groupcollide()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.sprite.spritecollideany&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.sprite.spritecollideany&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">spritecollideany()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="s0">).</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition note&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition-title&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Note</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">To increase performance, create and set a </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">attribute for all</span>
<span class="s0">sprites that will use this function to check for collisions. Otherwise,</span>
<span class="s0">each time this function is called it will create new masks.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition note&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition-title&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Note</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">A new mask needs to be recreated each time a sprite's image is changed</span>
<span class="s0">(e.g. if a new image is used or the existing image is rotated).</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig sig-object py title&quot; </span><span class="s2">id</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.sprite.groupcollide&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-prename descclassname&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.sprite.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-name descname&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">groupcollide</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-paren&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-paren&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;headerlink&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.sprite.groupcollide&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;Permalink to this definition&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0"></span><span class="s1">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line-block&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;summaryline&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Find all sprites that collide between two groups.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">groupcollide(group1, group2, dokill1, dokill2, collided = None) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Sprite_dict</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">This will find collisions between all the Sprites in two groups.</span>
<span class="s0">Collision is determined by comparing the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sprite.rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">attribute of</span>
<span class="s0">each Sprite or by using the collided function if it is not None.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Every Sprite inside group1 is added to the return dictionary. The value for</span>
<span class="s0">each item is the list of Sprites in group2 that intersect.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">If either dokill argument is True, the colliding Sprites will be removed</span>
<span class="s0">from their respective Group.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The collided argument is a callback function used to calculate if two sprites are</span>
<span class="s0">colliding. It should take two sprites as values and return a bool value</span>
<span class="s0">indicating if they are colliding. If collided is not passed, then all</span>
<span class="s0">sprites must have a </span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">rect</span><span class="s4">&amp;quot; </span><span class="s0">value, which is a rectangle of the sprite area,</span>
<span class="s0">which will be used to calculate the collision.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;dl </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;py function definition&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;dd&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line-block&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;summaryline&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Simple test if a sprite intersects anything in a group.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">spritecollideany(sprite, group, collided = None) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Sprite</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; </span><span class="s0">Collision with the returned sprite.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">spritecollideany(sprite, group, collided = None) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; </span><span class="s0">No collision</span><span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">If the sprite collides with any single sprite in the group, a single</span>
<span class="s0">sprite from the group is returned.  On no collision None is returned.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">If you don't need all the features of the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.sprite.spritecollide()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">function, this</span>
<span class="s0">function will be a bit quicker.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The collided argument is a callback function used to calculate if two sprites are</span>
<span class="s0">colliding. It should take two sprites as values and return a bool value</span>
<span class="s0">indicating if they are colliding. If collided is not passed, then all</span>
<span class="s0">sprites must have a </span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">rect</span><span class="s4">&amp;quot; </span><span class="s0">value, which is a rectangle of the sprite area,</span>
<span class="s0">which will be used to calculate the collision.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</span>
